--- !u!114 &1182926011
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1182926009}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: '- No walls, just a dark skybox. no acid below, just an invisible killbox
    that respawns you. Should feel kinda dreamy and otherworldly

    - the player
    enters and can cast a shadow on the wall using Shadow Shape. this lights up one
    of the indicators on the coffin and causes it to lower 1/4th the way down. then
    the wall drops letting them access the rest of the puzzle

    - Burnable Shadow
    Shapes is made up of various burnable objects, the right ones have to be burned
    to make it match the Complicated Shadow Indicator, at which point the player
    can cast the shadow and have the coffin drop another 1/4th

    - If the player
    burns the wrong part, the entire shape burns away and a new one drops from above

    -
    Lantern (1) can be entered (before or after second shadow puzzle) and ve used
    to travel to Lantern (2) or Lantern (3)

    - 3 is currently a dead end

    -
    2 leads to a refraction crystal, a gem, and a Shadow Indicator that can''t be
    accessed yet

    - When the Gem is activated, the Mirror activates (it''s like
    turned around or something beforehand

    - Player must split to have it on
    a shoot a light beam at the mirror to light the other lantern (they have to do
    it blindly so be forgiving with the hitbox

    - They can now return Lantern
    (3) to go to the (previously) unlit lantern

    - There they find a Gem (2)
    and Thin Shadow Indicator

    - Gem (2) makes the Inaccessable Shadow Indicator
    accessable so the second player can use the cystal to make a shodow and make
    the coffin drop 1/4th

    - The Thin Shadow Indicator requries both players
    to stand behind it to make a smaller shadow, making the coffin drop 1/4th

    -
    Once the coffin is all the way down, the player can blink dash to it (only from
    the first platform) and get to the end (where there''s a crystal to recombine)
    and leave through what I assume is like a glowing heavenly door'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2180264, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
